<p itemprop="description">A machine learning engineer develops, deploys, and maintains machine learning systems and models in production environments. They bridge the gap between data science research and operational ML systems, ensuring models are scalable, reliable, and performant.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Design and implement machine learning pipelines and model deployment systems</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Deploy and maintain machine learning models in production environments</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Optimise model performance, scalability, and reliability</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with data scientists to operationalise research and experiments</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Implement MLOps practices and automated model monitoring</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure ML systems comply with ethical and regulatory requirements</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Build tools and infrastructure to support machine learning workflows</li>
    </ul>
</section>

